I feel the need for Feign to be up at all time for different reasons<br>
<br>
1) Solo - Well that's obvious. <br>
2) Grouped - I am the only class that can survive a wipe and rez without leaving the pull sight (logging,gating)<br>
3) Raid - Same as 2<br>
<br>
I find the need to stay alive both in line with my own personal agenda as well as everyone elses. (I love being a Necro!)<br>
<br>
Yitamen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fayrnn>Fayrnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 12:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3916.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Casters who gate out of losing battles...</span><hr size=1> I think that it is up to the group or raid leader to call the shot: either camp or gate or zone or stand your ground . . . and in a few circumstances even maybe choice (meaning it is up to the individual caster).<br>
<br>
As a cleric I am in a tough spot. I am the life-blood of my group or raid. I HAVE to follow orders first off - and that took me awhile to learn. At first I stayed and did not read the lines - I sometimes stayed and healed (when I was young I  fought because my mana was gone). When the leader called Gate or camp I missed the order and died.<br>
<br>
Sometimes I saw the order to run or zone and got lost and died. I have a hard time finding my way in areas -- This leads me to find a spot away from the general spawn areas - try to hold the aggro away from the group who is trying to zone and then die heh. At least it gives them a chance to get the hell out.<br>
<br>
Gating when told is a good option - gives me a chance to get back and rez with all my gear, weapons, KEI and WIS.<br>
<br>
Camping can be a very dangerous hit and miss - especially in high level areas because as soon as CAMP is called - and I sit down - my aggro goes WAY WAY up. AND usually its because the tank is already badly hurt and doesn't have long to live anyway . . . takes 30 seconds to camp. That's one hell of a long time for a really pissed off mob to kill off the tank, clean its claws, look around, smile, amble over and kill my ass.<br>
<br>
Gate is a good option. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeitraffer>Zeitraffer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3916.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Casters who gate out of losing battles...</span><hr size=1> I play a shaman alt and i have 6 perma slots and 2 i switch out I cant find any room for gate<br>
