 I MEAN last man standing!! I have many times been in the depths of a dungeon on my own knowing damn well that as soon as the spawn timers resets I am going to be overwhelmed with mobs.<br>
<br>
The way it works for me is.. If everyone is dead/fleeing and I am left I will wait until my pet is half health and then gate. I basically use my pet as a shield to give me and whoever else time to get to safety. I have to have this memmed as everyone who has a pet knows, if a caster sits down to memm something when pets soloing, the mob will forget the pet and come straight for you! If there is anyone left I will never gate. I didnt get run 3 for no reason at all you know, besides.. I hate having to make my way back to the Dungeon cause I gated.<br>
<br>
I have only used gate by mistake once!! I was drunk and hadnt slept for 2 days and mapped a shortcut key to my gate instead of mala so..<br>
<br>
/group Casting Mala on %t * <br>
Noggy Fades away<br>
